<subSubSection lastPageId="57" lastPageNumber="58" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="56.[136,1452,1850,2056]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis box="[136,217,1850,1876]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Annual</emphasis>
, rosetted, acaulescent (sometimes with short fragile column towards the end of the growing season). 
<emphasis box="[1374,1452,1851,1876]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Leaves</emphasis>
semi-erect or decumbent, with entire-involute vernation; petiole gradually broadening into lamina; lamina obovate, with conspicuous unifacial marginal glands (“snap-tentacles”) on the marginal apex, and densely minutely glandularpilose on both surfaces; stipules rectangular in outline, fimbriate. 
<emphasis box="[874,952,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Scapes</emphasis>
erect at the base, glabrous, with a ceraceous appearance; sepals glandular-pilose; petals pink; ovary 5-merous, styles 5, entire, stigmata with long papillae. 
<emphasis box="[1388,1452,1994,2020]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Seeds</emphasis>
ovoid, black, testa reticulate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="57.[136,1452,158,2056]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,292,158,184]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Illustrations:</emphasis>
— 
<bibRefCitation author="Saint-Hilaire, A. F. C. P. de" box="[320,539,158,184]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" refId="ref58205" refString="Saint-Hilaire, A. F. C. P. de (1826) Histoire des plantes les plus remarquables du Bresil et du Paraguay 1 (6). A. Belin, Paris [exact content of part 6 unknown]." type="book" year="1826">Saint-Hilaire (1826</bibRefCitation>
: t. XXV, figs.A &amp; 1—habit and gynoecium); Eichler (1872: t. 90, fig. I—habit and details); 
<bibRefCitation author="Hoehne, F. C." box="[234,397,194,221]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="26 - 28" refId="ref56312" refString="Hoehne, F. C. (1915) Droseraceae. Commissao de Linhas Telegraphicas, Botanica 6: 26 - 28 + Tab. 124." type="journal article" year="1915">Hoehne (1915</bibRefCitation>
: t. 124, fig. 1—habit and details); 
<bibRefCitation author="Diels, L." box="[782,960,194,220]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="1 - 136" refId="ref54188" refString="Diels, L. (1906) Droseraceae. In: Engler, H. G. A. (ed.) Das Pflanzenreich IV. 112 (Heft 26). W. Engelmann, Leipzig, pp. 1 - 136." type="book chapter" year="1906">Diels (1906: 74</bibRefCitation>
, figs. 27A–D—leaf, calyx and gynoecium); 
<bibRefCitation author="Silva, T. R. S. &amp; Giulietti, A. M." box="[136,440,230,256]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="75 - 105" refId="ref59136" refString="Silva, T. R. S. &amp; Giulietti, A. M. (1997) Levantamento das Droseraceae do Brasil. Boletim de Botanica da Universidade de Sao Paulo 16: 75 - 105." type="journal article" year="1997">
<taxonomicName authority="Gonella &amp; Sano &amp; Rivadavia &amp; Fleischmann, 2022" authorityName="Gonella &amp; Sano &amp; Rivadavia &amp; Fleischmann" authorityYear="2022" box="[136,194,230,256]" class="Aves" family="Leiothrichidae" genus="Silva" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="57" pageNumber="74" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="N.G.">Silva</taxonomicName>
&amp; Giulietti (1997: 84
</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 5); 
<bibRefCitation author="Duno de Stefano, R. &amp; Culham, A." box="[535,981,230,257]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="697 - 703" refId="ref54421" refString="Duno de Stefano, R. &amp; Culham, A. (1998) Droseraceae. In: Steyermark, J. A., Berry, P. E. &amp; Holst, B. K. (eds.) Flora of the Venezuelan Guayana 4. Missouri Botanical Garden Press, St Louis, pp. 697 - 703." type="book chapter" year="1998">Duno de Stefano &amp; Culham (1998: 701</bibRefCitation>
